Wash and dry all produce. Halve @baby red potatoes{10%oz}, then place in a #medium pot{} with a large pinch of @salt{pinch} and enough water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and reduce to a simmer. Cook until just tender, about ~{6%minutes}. Drain.

Meanwhile, peel, halve, and finely chop @shallot{1}(peeled and finely chopped) until you have 1 TBSP. Chop @tarragon{1/4%oz} and @parsley{1/4%oz} until you have 1 TBSP of each. Halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise, then slice crosswise into 1 1/2-inch-long pieces. Using the back of a #chef's knife{}, smash @garlic{2%cloves}(smashed), then cut each clove in half. Halve @lemon{1}, then squeeze 1 TBSP juice into a #small bowl{}.

Heat 1 TBSP @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season @chicken breasts{12%oz} all over with @salt{} and a pinch of @white pepper{pinch} (we sent more). Add to pan and sear until browned, ~{4%minutes} per side.

Heat 1 TBSP olive oil in another large pan over medium heat. Add potatoes, cut-side down, along with garlic. Increase heat to medium-high and cook until potatoes start to brown, about ~{2%minutes}. Add zucchini and cook, tossing, until lightly browned and tender, about ~{6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Remove pan from heat and stir in half the tarragon and parsley.

Stir shallot, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, reserved lemon juice, and ½ cup water into pan with chicken. Let cook until chicken is no longer pink in center, ~{4-5%minutes} longer. Transfer chicken to a #plate{}, keeping sauce in pan. Whisk @Dijon mustard{1%tsp} into pan (we sent more), then bring mixture to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and let simmer until reduced to a saucy consistency, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once sauce has reduced, stir in remaining tarragon and parsley. Remove pan from heat. Stir in @sour cream{4%tbsp}. Divide veggies and chicken between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken and serve.